    "description": "An M5 depth surface carries a Stable (or LTS) claim only when its cross-surface hardening scorecard passes every dimension (onboarding/migration truth, design-token and component-state parity, durable-attention semantics, embedded-boundary integrity, exact-target reopen expectations, and qualification currency), the redaction/provenance support posture is disclosed, the proof packet is current within its freshness SLO, any waiver is unexpired, the owner manifest is signed, and its downgrade automation is defined and its frozen-fallback rollback plan verified. A surface that loses any of those must drop below the cutline rather than inherit an adjacent hardened surface."
  },
